## Comment Guidelines

### When to Comment

✅ **Comment these**:
- Complex algorithms
- Non-obvious business logic
- Magic numbers (or better, extract to config!)
- Workarounds for bugs
- Performance optimizations

❌ **Don't comment these**:
- Obvious code
- What code does (code should be self-explanatory)
- Commented-out code (delete it, use git)

### Comment Style

```javascript
// ✅ GOOD: Explains WHY
// Using binary search because array is pre-sorted
// and can have 10k+ elements
const index = binarySearch(array, target);

// ❌ BAD: Explains WHAT (obvious from code)
// Loop through the array
for (let i = 0; i < array.length; i++) { }
```

### Magic Numbers

Always explain OR extract to config:

```javascript
// ❌ BAD: What is 64? Why 64?
if (tile.size === 64) { }

// ✅ BETTER: Comment explains
// 64 is the tile size used in all game graphics
if (tile.size === 64) { }

// ✅ BEST: Extract to config
if (tile.size === CONFIG.TILE_SIZE) { }
```

