## Git Commit Standards

### Commit Message Format

```
{type}({scope}): {description}

[optional body]
```

### Types
- `feat`: New feature
- `fix`: Bug fix
- `refactor`: Code restructuring
- `docs`: Documentation
- `test`: Test additions
- `style`: Formatting, no logic change
- `perf`: Performance improvement
- `chore`: Maintenance

### Scopes
[Project-specific - define based on your components]

### Examples

```
feat(player): add double-jump ability
fix(collision): resolve ghost collisions at high speed
refactor(render): split 800-line renderer into focused components
docs(api): add JSDoc comments to public methods
```

### When to Commit

Only after:
1. Feature works
2. Code tested
3. User confirmed it works

Never before:
- Code compiles but not tested
- Known bugs exist
- User hasn't verified

